<h2 class="bold font-l">The Service Weapon</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Jesse Faden finds herself unexpectedly participating in a test of her worthiness to become the new Director of the Federal Bureau of Control - by being nudged into picking up the ex-director's Service Weapon and plunged into the Astral Plane, with the warning that failing will result in the weapon blowing her head off. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="ayzp1u" data-video-descrip="Parodied in the Postal film adaptation: the interview process for one Incompetence, Inc. involves ever more surreal and nonsensical questions, asked by a hostile stenographer who doesn't even bother to wait for answers, until the Postal Guy snaps entirely. His outburst gets him to the top of the list." data-video-title="Postal" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/ayzp1u_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/ayzp1u.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/IncomprehensibleEntranceExam" data-video-tropename="Incomprehensible Entrance Exam" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/Postal" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/ayzp1u.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Postal</span></p>
